-- CNPC Shuts Some Natural Gas Wells in Chongqing on Floods After Heavy Rain
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-07-12T02:40:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-12/cnpc-shuts-some-natural-gas-wells-in-chongqing-on-floods-after-heavy-rain.html

          
          
             China National Petroleum Corp. has
shut some gas wells in Chongqing in southwestern China, the
company said in a statement today.  
 The wells were shut after heavy rainfall caused flooding,
the oil and gas producer said, without giving details.  
